Eden Hazard is favourite to win the PFA Player of the Year award this season . 
  Chelsea playmaker is closing in on a first Premier League title . 
  Paul Scholes believes Hazard needs to be more ruthless to be compared with Cristiano Ronaldo and Lionel Messi . 
  Hazard has scored 13 goals and made eight assists in 32 games . 
  Harry Kane is also in the running for the award . 
 